\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 61. G. murcicum} Boiss. & Reuter in Boiss.,{\i  Diagn. Pl. Or. Nov. }{\b 3}({\b 2}): 114 (1856). Stolons present. Stems 40-90 cm, glabrous. Leaves 10-25 × 0·5-2 mm, in whorls of 6-7, linear, glabrous; margin slightly scabrid with 1 to 2 rows of teeth, revolute to the midrib. Inflorescence broadly ovoid, distinctly interrupted; flowers in dense clusters; pedicels much shorter than diameter of corolla. Corolla 3-4 mm in diameter, infundibuliform; tube shorter than lobes.{\i  Calcareous, stony ground. • S.E. Spain.} Hs.
