\pard\f0\fs28  Ser. {\i Nemoralia} M. Popov. Young shoots green or glaucous and pruinose. Stems terete to 4-angled. Leaves elliptical to linear-lanceolate, usually 25-75 mm; lower surface paler green than the upper and often bluish. Inflorescence broadly ovoid, lax, with long lower branches; partial inflorescences corymbiform; pedicels often capillary, not divaricate after anthesis. Corolla white, cup-shaped to rotate; tube shorter than lobes; lobes acute to apiculate.
\par 

